  "text": "The kubernetes/kubernetes repository implements pod eviction on node memory pressure through the eviction manager system located in pkg/kubelet/eviction/. Here are the key components:\n\n## Memory Pressure Threshold Definition\n\nMemory pressure thresholds are defined as signals in pkg/kubelet/eviction/api/types.go (line 29-30, 53-54):\n- SignalMemoryAvailable: memory capacity minus working set\n- SignalAllocatableMemoryAvailable: allocatable memory minus pod working set\n\nThresholds are configured via pkg/kubelet/apis/config/types.go (EvictionHard, EvictionSoft) and parsed by ParseThresholdConfig() in pkg/kubelet/eviction/helpers.go (line 119).\n\n## Eviction Manager Decision Logic\n\nThe main eviction manager implementation is in pkg/kubelet/eviction/eviction_manager.go:\n\n1. **Manager Initialization**: NewManager() creates the manager instance (line 115), and Start() (line 184) begins monitoring with a control loop that calls synchronize() periodically.\n\n2. **Core Decision Loop**: The synchronize() function (line 243) is the main control loop that:\n   - Gets memory observations via makeSignalObservations() (line 306)\n   - Evaluates which thresholds are met by comparing available memory to threshold values\n   - Determines node conditions (memory pressure) from met thresholds\n   - Tracks grace periods before evicting pods\n   - Ranks pods using rankMemoryPressure() for eviction priority\n   - Calls evictPod() when thresholds are met and grace periods satisfied\n\n3. **Threshold Evaluation**: thresholdsMet() in pkg/kubelet/eviction/helpers.go (line 934) compares:\n   - Observed available memory (from makeMemoryAvailableSignalObservation() in helpers_others.go)\n   - Against configured threshold values using LessThan operator\n   - Returns met thresholds that trigger eviction\n\n4. **Node Condition Tracking**: nodeConditions() (line 1038 in helpers.go) maps memory thresholds to v1.NodeMemoryPressure conditions. These are reported via syncNodeStatus() in pkg/kubelet/kubelet_node_status.go (line 780).\n\n5. **Pod Admission**: The Admit() function (line 146 in eviction_manager.go) prevents admission of best-effort pods when the node has memory pressure, allowing only guaranteed and burstable pods with memory requests.\n\n## Memory Observation Calculation\n\nMemory available is calculated in makeMemoryAvailableSignalObservation() (helpers_others.go, line 27):\n- Available = summary.Node.Memory.AvailableBytes\n- Capacity = AvailableBytes + WorkingSetBytes\n\nThreshold quantities are resolved by GetThresholdQuantity() in pkg/kubelet/eviction/api/types.go (line 111), supporting both absolute quantities (e.g., 1Gi) and percentages.\n\n## Kernel Integration\n\nOn Linux with KernelMemcgNotification enabled, memory threshold notifiers in memory_threshold_notifier_linux.go provide efficient kernel-based cgroup memory pressure detection instead of polling."
}

